Outline Audit is a small JavaScript program that walks a document’s heading structure and reports problems: skipped levels, empty headings, suspicious patterns and anything else that makes the outline hard to follow for users and for assistive technology.

## Miscellaneous

I built Outline Audit in 2016 and announced it in *[Introducing Outline Audit](/2016/03/30/introducing-outline-audit/)* as part of my work at Edenspiekermann. It was a practical way to catch heading mistakes before they shipped, especially on large content-heavy sites where headings are edited by many people.